summary:
Sure, here is a summary of the video:

**Overview**
The video explains the differences between an AI agent and agentic AI, as well as the differences in terms of their functions.

**Key Points**
- The presenter defines AI agent as an independent system or tool that can handle only one specific job autonomously and it has a predefined set of rules and goals. 
- Examples of an AI agent include an AI chatbot or an AI agent which can help to write a resume.
- On the other hand, agentic AI is not just one agent. It is a design approach which handles the entire workflow.
- Agentic AI is considered as a team working together to get you hired, using research agents, custom resume creation, and interview preparation. 
- Bottom line, AI agents prefer to work alone. On the other hand, agentic AI prefers to collaborate as a team.
